## Placement rules
<!-- AI: For each common file type, state exactly where it goes. These are hard rules. -->
| File type | Goes in | Example |
|-----------|---------|--------|
| UI components | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/components/ -->` | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/components/Button.tsx -->` |
| API route handlers | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/app/api/ -->` | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/app/api/users/route.ts -->` |
| Business logic | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/services/ -->` | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/services/userService.ts -->` |
| Database queries | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/lib/db/ -->` | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/lib/db/users.ts -->` |
| Types / interfaces | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/types/ -->` | `<!-- AI: e.g. src/types/user.ts -->` |
| Unit tests | Mirror `src/` in `tests/unit/` | `<!-- AI: e.g. tests/unit/services/userService.test.ts -->` |
| E2E tests | `tests/e2e/` | `<!-- AI: e.g. tests/e2e/login.spec.ts -->` |

## What must never happen
- Business logic in route handlers or components — put it in the service layer.
- Database calls outside of the DB layer.
- Shared types defined inside a single component or route file.
- Test files mixed into `src/` directories.
